            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39911",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My idea was to have a class, let's call it Zend_Mail_Storage_Set, supporting UIDs, ranges, search, sort, ... An instance of a storage class would have a method set(), which returns a set instance (common or specialized for this storage). A couple of features are not IMAP specific and it wouldn't make sense to just add a new method for one storage.\r\n\r\nZend_Mail_Storage_Set would implement an iterator interface and instead of getting just an id or UID you could also fetch the corresponding message. I have an old mail with a couple of use cases.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-09T09:41:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-09T09:41:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39912",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sounds good as long as it is fast. For example if you want to retrieve messages with UID 1-5, it should only call one IMAP command and not 5. \r\nThe same for moving messages, deleting messages and so on. See also my other issues ZF-9138 ZF-8513 ZF-8488",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mkliewe",
                        "name": "mkliewe",
                        "displayName": "Michael Kliewe",
